# Frontend Rules (Auto-Applied)

## Package Manager: Bun ONLY

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Install | `bun install` |
| CI install | `bun install --frozen-lockfile` |
| Run scripts | `bun run <script>` |
| Run tools | `bunx <tool>` |
| Test | `bun run test` (Jest via Bun) |
| Build | `bun run build` |

**NEVER use npm, npx, or yarn. NEVER create package-lock.json.**

- Lock file: `bun.lock` (must be committed)
- `package.json` must have `"packageManager": "bun@latest"`
- CI workflow uses `oven-sh/setup-bun@v2` (not setup-node)

## Before Committing Frontend Changes

Run these checks and fix any failures before committing:

```bash
cd frontend
bun run build   # Must compile with zero errors
bun run test    # All tests must pass
bun run lint    # Zero ESLint warnings/errors
bunx tsc --noEmit  # Zero TypeScript errors
```

## Responsive Design Standards

All frontend components must be mobile-first responsive:

- Horizontal padding: `px-4 sm:px-6` (never bare `px-6`)
- Section vertical padding: `py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24`
- Headings: `text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl` (progressive scale)
- Hero heading: `text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl`
- Buttons: `flex-col sm:flex-row` for stacking on mobile
- Code blocks: wrap in `overflow-x-auto` container
- Icons next to text: add `shrink-0` to icon, `min-w-0` to text container
- Tables: provide mobile card alternative with `hidden sm:block` / `sm:hidden`
